age of happy numbers = }\\frac{\\text{number of happy 0s + number of happy 1s}} {\\text{total numbers}}\\times \\left (100\\right)$$\n","\n","In the example above, percentage of happy numbers is $60 \\%$ ."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"AtvPTG3kpBoS"},"source":["# Solution :\n"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"ljMMN4Hnd10p"},"source":["In the above program we have passed `numbers[]` list as a parameter inside the `percentage_happy()` function where `numbers[]` hold the list of `0`s and `1`s\n","\n","- First we have intialized a variable `happy` with value `0`.\n","\n","- If the number in first position and second position are same then we are incrementing the value of happy by `1` which means that they both are happy.\n","\n","- Similarly if the numbers in the last and second last position are same then we are again incrementing the value of happy by `1` which means that they both are happy.\n","\n","- Then using a `for` loop we are iterating through the elements in the list `numbers[]`.\n","\n","- Using `if` condition we are checking whether the left element of list `numbers[i-1]` is equal to the right element of that list `numbers[i-1]` and if they both are equal we are incrementing the value of happy by `1`.\n","\n","- Finally we are calculating the percentage of happy numbers in the `numbers[]` list by dividing the value of `happy` with the length of numbers `len(numbers)` and multiplying it with 100.\n","\n","    "]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"KOVBiUSMzut1"},"source":["---"]}]}